# Salesforce Project Rules

This is a Salesforce **org development model** project. Metadata lives in `src/` (source format). All Salesforce CLI work uses **sf CLI v2** — never legacy `sfdx force:*` commands.

## Branch Rules

The `{{defaultBranch}}` branch mirrors production and must **never** be committed to directly. Every change goes through a feature branch and the Bitbucket pull-request pipeline.

## Deployment Workflow

1. **Build Package** (automatic on PR) — syncs production into `{{defaultBranch}}`, merges it into the PR branch, and builds an incremental deployment package with sfdx-git-delta (including `destructiveChanges.xml` when needed).
2. **Check Package** (manual) — runs a check-only deployment with tests; results appear on the PR.
3. **Quick Deploy** (manual) — performs the quick deploy, auto-merges the branch into `{{defaultBranch}}`, and deletes the feature branch.

## Preview a Deployment Package Locally

Run the **SF: Preview Deployment Package** task (or `sf sgd source delta --from "origin/{{defaultBranch}}" --to HEAD --output-dir dist --generate-delta`) to see what would be deployed.

## PR Description Flags

- `!skipSync` — skip the production sync during Build Package.
- `!tests=Foo,Bar` — run only the listed Apex test classes during Check Package.

## Formatting

Prettier formats Apex and LWC on commit via the pre-commit hook.

